                ✔ 7-B per-instance cursed relics @done(26-07-14) (SCAFFOLD ONLY — no gameplay effect until 7-C wires the flag into the cursed-augmented perk pool. RelicTierEntry gains BaseCurseChanceModifier; per-relic modifiers authored (breakers/defects/vulnerability relics get +0.05-0.10, safer Solo -0.05, flagship Legendaries +0.15). Config knobs RelicBaseCurseChance=0.15, EscalationCurseChancePerScalar=0.03. Pure CursedRelicRoll.ChanceFor(entry, scalar, active, base, bonus) formula = clamp01(base + relic_mod + scalar*bonus), returns 0 if escalation is dormant. Cursed roll only fires post-activation. Spawn-time Harmony postfix on LootOnDeathDropper.SpawnLootInCurrentPosition scans nearby CarryableObjects, marks known relics via CursedRelicMarker component using UnityEngine.Random on host. Idempotent via CursedProcessedMarker sentinel. CommitRequest extended with RelicIsCursed[] FIFO — UpgradeForgeBehavior.TryCommit reads markers; calculator ignores the flag for now (7-C will consume). Dev cmds !cursedstatus (nearest 5 relics with tier, cursed flag, and computed chance breakdown), !forcecursed <on|off> (nearest relic). 11 xunit tests on pure ChanceFor / ShouldBeCursed math. Multiplayer sync deferred to Phase 8 — currently host-only.)
                ✔ 7-C Maintenance Burden (Option W'' — cursed adds burden, does not affect perk) @done(26-07-14) (Design departed from doc's "cursed-augmented perk pool" — cursed relics do NOT get a different perk pool. Perk roll unchanged from 7-A. Instead: on successful commit consuming ≥1 cursed relic, INDEPENDENT burden roll (BurdenApplicationChance=0.5) decides whether the target module also gets a Maintenance Burden. Perk + burden are orthogonal outcomes of the same commit. New BurdenType enum (None, RandomShutoff — extensible). CommitOutcome.AppliedBurden. ForgeSnapshot.Burdens IReadOnlyList<BurdenType> + WithBurdenAdded builder — different burden TYPES stack on one module but never duplicates. Pre-flight verified CellModule.TurnOff()/TurnOn() as the right power API. RandomShutoffBehavior : MaintenanceBurdenBehavior MonoBehaviour: seeded RNG per module ViewID for MP convergence, calls TurnOff for BurdenShutoffMin-Max seconds (default 2-4), then TurnOn, waits BurdenIntervalMin-Max (default 30-90), repeats. Notifications on shutoff + recovery. ForgeModuleState.BuildMods stamps Burden_RandomShutoff CsTag via zero-value marker (matches Forge_Upgraded pattern) for game-visible queries. Utils.CsTagRegistry.BurdenRandomShutoff + BurdenTagFor(BurdenType) helper. Snapshot bridges deconstruct/reconstruct — burdens survive the rebuild. Dev cmds !listburdens, !triggerburden. 11 new xunit tests (snapshot burdens + calculator burden roll). Multiplayer sync of AppliedBurden state deferred to Phase 8.)
                ✔ 7-C refinement: per-relic BurdenAffinity @done(26-07-14) (Each cursed relic declares which burden types it can inflict via RelicTierEntry.BurdenAffinity: IReadOnlyList<BurdenType>. Calculator's RollBurden now accumulates the union of affinity types across consumed cursed relics, then uniformly picks one after the chance gate passes. All 29 relics default to [RandomShutoff] (only shipped burden type — behavior identical today). When 7-D and future burden types land, per-relic overrides can encode lore fit — temperature/biomass relics → HeatTick, defects → ManualReset, breakers → RandomShutoff. 2 additional xunit tests for the affinity lookup + null-name defensive skip.)
                ✔ 7-C refinement: bake burden at spawn time @done(26-07-14) (Curse identity is now fully fixed at spawn — CursedRelicMarker.BakedBurden carries the specific BurdenType the relic will inflict. Spawn patch picks uniformly from RelicTierEntry.BurdenAffinity when cursed roll passes; the specific burden is stored on the marker component. CommitRequest.RelicIsCursed[] renamed to RelicCursedBurden[] carrying BurdenType (None = not cursed). Calculator RollBurden simplified — no more affinity gathering + pool pick at commit time; walks consumed relics FIFO for the first non-None baked burden, applies with high-chance gate. BurdenApplicationChance default raised 0.5 → 0.75 per "high chance" design intent. !cursedstatus now shows the baked burden alongside cursed flag; !forcecursed <on|off> [burdenType] optionally accepts a burden type. New CursedRelicMarker.GetBurden(GameObject) → BurdenType helper. Signature semantics unchanged (perk vs burden still orthogonal).)
